import React, { Component } from 'react'; class Home2 extends React.Component { render() { return ( < div > < div className = "jumbotron jumbotron-fluid cover" > < div className = "container text-color" > < h1 className = "intro-name" > Hi!I 'm Maylen < p className = "intro-description" > a Front - End Developer and UX / UI Designer < /p> < /div> < /div> < section className = "about-section size" > < div className = "container" > < p className = "intro" > Hello, my name is Maylen.A passionate Front - End Developer and UX / UI designer based in Sydney. < /p> < div className = "info" > < p > I 'm passionate about travel, collaboration and shaping new designers through my activities as a blogger, speaker and course author.

< p > I have 4 years of experience in designing and building highly scalable web applications.I mostly work with JavaScript, React JS, Node JS, GraphQL and Sketch.I 'm also fluent with build tools like Webpack and Parcel, transpilers like Babel and Typescript, CIs like GoCD and Travis. I care a lot about user experience, minimalism, reusability and clean code.

< p > Drop me an email for any new opportunities. < /p> < /div> < div className = "links" > < div className = "row" > < div className = "col-sm-12" > < a href = "#" id = "git" target = "_blank" > < i class = "fab fa-github fa-2x" > < /i> < a href = "#" id = "linkedin" target = "_blank" > < i class = "fab fa-linkedin-in fa-2x" > < /i> < a href = "#" id = "facebook" target = "_blank" > < i class = "mr-3 fab fa-facebook-square fa-2x" > < /i> < /div> < /div> < /div> < /div> < /section> < section className = "portfolio-section" > { /*

A lovely selection of work

*/ } < /section> < section className = "contact-me-section pv-6" > < div className = "container" > < h1 className = "intro-name" > CONTACT. < /h1> < p className = "intro-description" > Want to work together ? Tell me about your project < /p> < /div> < /section> < /div> ); } } export default Home2;
